invariants:
  - Preserve the exact root ranking kernel and stable debug hooks.
  - IndexedDB is canonical working state, not a promise against browser eviction.
  - One shared corpus module owns schema upgrades; root clients open the current version without pinning it.
  - Request persistent storage and report best-effort status honestly.
  - Corpus mutations and compatibility receipts commit atomically.
  - Full-file hashing must not run on the main thread when Worker and Web Crypto exist.
  - Heavy media hydrates near the viewport only and releases object URLs when cold.
  - Video and audio sources must be detached before their object URLs are revoked.
  - Magic bytes and content outrank absent or contradictory MIME metadata.
  - Unknown binary must never be decoded into feed text.
  - Every local record may be deleted; shared assets may not be removed while referenced.
  - Feed Full and Desktop may change layout physics but never ranking records or action semantics.
  - Every visible custom product control must come from the action contract and exist when its surface becomes visible.
  - Fixed chrome must never make a physically covered control count as a passing touch target.
  - Temporary proof content may exist only inside test journeys and must be gone before the browser context closes.
  - Static compatibility may replace only a missing starter endpoint and must not impersonate profile or remote persistence.
  - Backend identity must not persist the raw local device secret.
  - Remote principals are opaque capability holders and must not encode vendors models companies or permanent collaboration roles.
  - Remote message payloads remain project-defined and open-ended.
  - Remote messages are append-only and retrieval is cursor-based.
  - Private credentials signatures private payloads and write authority must never enter consumer code or repository content.
  - A terminal session generation cannot silently resume; further work requires a new generation or session.
  - Every successful terminal check must identify the exact tested Git head.
  - A deployed production receipt must name the exact merge SHA.
  - The public LIVE terminal may expose only explicitly public projections.
  - REMOTE_WORK.md REMOTE_THOUGHT.md and generation metadata are discovery pointers not live-state ledgers.
  - Do not add a second engineering-belief ledger or duplicate runtime schema authority.
  - Never use or persist credentials pasted into chat.
